67 Mill Lane, at the N.E. corner of Kings Highway, showing the J.C. Ryder home; built by Stoothoff in 1800, and owned by W. Reed in 1860. It came into the hands of Ryder in 1873.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, a closer view.

March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

67 Mill Lane, at the N.E. corner of Kings Highway, showing the J.J. Ryder House built in 1800 by one of the Stoothoff's; occupied by J. C. Ryder in 1873 and later by John J. Ryder; razed in 1925.

1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same; a rear view, from Kings Highway.

1922.
